%% Enterprise AI Workflow Platform — RAG data flow
%% Document upload through chat citation
%% Render: mmdc -i data-flow-rag.mmd -o data-flow-rag.png -t default -b transparent
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant U as User
  participant W as Next.js Web
  participant A as FastAPI Gateway
  participant S as MinIO (S3)
  participant P as Postgres + pgvector
  participant K as Redpanda
  participant I as Ingestion Worker
  participant E as Embedding Worker
  participant G as LLM Gateway
  participant L as LLM Provider

  Note over U,A: Phase 1 — upload
  U->>W: select PDF
  W->>A: POST /v1/documents (multipart)
  A->>S: PutObject(bytes)
  A->>P: INSERT documents (status=uploaded, org_id, workspace_id)
  A->>K: produce documents.uploaded.v1<br/>{document_id, org_id, s3_key, traceparent}
  A-->>W: 202 Accepted {document_id, status: uploaded}

  Note over K,I: Phase 2 — parse + chunk
  K-->>I: consume documents.uploaded.v1
  I->>S: GetObject(s3_key)
  I->>I: parse (Unstructured) + chunk
  I->>P: INSERT chunks (embedding=NULL)
  I->>P: UPDATE documents SET status=parsed
  I->>K: produce documents.parsed.v1<br/>{document_id, chunk_ids[]}

  Note over K,E: Phase 3 — embed
  K-->>E: consume documents.parsed.v1
  E->>L: embed batch (via provider abstraction)
  L-->>E: vectors
  E->>P: UPDATE chunks SET embedding = $vec, embedding_model_version = $v
  E->>P: UPDATE documents SET status=ready
  E->>K: produce documents.embedded.v1

  Note over U,L: Phase 4 — chat with citations (later)
  U->>W: ask question
  W->>A: POST /v1/conversations/:id/messages (Accept: text/event-stream)
  A->>P: SET LOCAL app.current_org_id = $org
  A->>P: hybrid search (vector + pg_trgm) → top_k chunks
  A->>G: complete_streaming(messages, retrieved_context, tools=[])
  G->>L: provider streaming call
  loop tokens arrive
    L-->>G: token delta
    G-->>A: ProviderEvent.TokenDelta
    A-->>W: SSE event: token
  end
  G-->>A: ProviderEvent.Stop
  A-->>W: SSE event: citation (per cited chunk_id)
  A-->>W: SSE event: end
  A->>P: INSERT messages (assistant) + message_citations
  A->>K: produce conversations.message.v1 (for usage accounting)
